    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-07-31T16:19:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-07-31T16:19:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">974.5301/7–3152: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 465<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d465fn1">Repeated to Paris, New York, Cairo, and Tel
                        Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-07-31T17:19:00-04:00"
                            >July 31, 1952—5:19 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>707. Dept has informed Brit and <gloss target="#t_Fr1">Fr</gloss> Embs receipt
                    Israeli note dated July 28<note n="2" xml:id="d465fn2">Not printed, but see the
                        circular airgram, <ref target="#d481">Document 481</ref>.</note> which urges
                    US secure Egypt compliance <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> Res Sep 1, 1951 on
                    Suez restrictions and states Israel wld welcome indication from US re means
                    which we propose adopt ensure free passage Canal. Dept suggesting that US UK and
                        <gloss target="#t_Fr1">Fr</gloss> replies shld be coordinated in Wash. Dept
                    also indicated that its thinking re Israeli note still along lines views set
                    forth <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 443, May 22 to NY.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
